(Description)
Reverse bits of a given 32 bits signed integer.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public int reverseBits(int n) {
        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
            result = (result << 1) | (n & 1);
            n >>= 1;
        }

        return result;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
(What I learned)
Bits calculator, << and >> was what I essentially learned today.

Because the size of bits was fixed at the description as 32, that makes the condition of for loop, i < 32.
Inside of for loop, result was moved to left at first, making the most right side fixed to 0.
Therefore, added value to result is follwed by (n & 1), if right side of n is 0, it is 1, otherwise it would add 0.
Then, n >>= 1 move given number n's digits to right by 1 bit, that helps to calculate exact values.
